OVN-Kubernetes gateway and ipForwarding:
- https://access.redhat.com/solutions/7053694 — Pods using routingViaHost with secondary interface for br-ex cannot route to default Kubernetes service IP. Related to how OVN-Kubernetes handles routing with secondary interfaces.
- https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/openshift_container_platform/4.16/html/networking/ovn-kubernetes-network-plugin — OVN-Kubernetes network plugin docs covering gateway modes, br-ex, and ipForwarding settings.

MetalLB on OpenShift:
- https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/openshift_container_platform/4.20/html/ingress_and_load_balancing/load-balancing-with-metallb — MetalLB L2 and BGP configuration, L2Advertisement, IPAddressPool setup.

